00:30.722 --> 00:34.287
Hello friends, I'm Rick Warren, and welcome to Spurgeon's Sermons.

00:34.747 --> 00:39.514
This is the official podcast brought to you by Premier and Spurgeon's College.

00:40.154 --> 00:48.285
You know the teachings of Charles Spurgeon have had a personal impact on my life in a profound way, and I'm confident they'll do the same for you.

00:48.425 --> 00:57.938
So get ready to be challenged, equipped, and guided by Charles Spurgeon, who is universally regarded as the greatest English preacher in the history of the church.

01:00.834 --> 01:06.601
the dream of Pilate's wife, a sermon by Charles Spurgeon, part two.

01:08.263 --> 01:21.840
When he was sat down on the judgment seat, his wife sent unto him, saying, Have nothing to do with that just man, for I have suffered many things this day in a dream because of him.

01:23.442 --> 01:29.650
Matthew's Gospel, chapter 27, verse 19.

01:30.018 --> 01:35.243
I call your attention to the cooperation of Providence with the work of God.

01:36.405 --> 01:50.600
I call it the work of God to warn men against sin, and I call your attention to Providence working with it to bring the preventives and cautions of divine mercy home to men's minds.

01:52.041 --> 01:56.786
For first, observe the Providence of God in sending this dream.

01:58.146 --> 02:07.298
If anything beneath the moon may be thought to be exempt from the law, and to be the creature of pure chance, surely it is a dream.

02:08.539 --> 02:13.706
True, there were in old time dreams in which God spoke to men prophetically.

02:14.547 --> 02:21.515
But ordinarily, they are the carnival of thought, a maze of mental states, a dance of disorder.

02:22.757 --> 02:26.802
The dreams which would naturally come to the wife of a Roman governor

02:27.362 --> 02:36.856
would not be likely to have much of tenderness or conscience in them, and would not in all probability of themselves running the line of mercy.

02:38.038 --> 02:46.290
Dreams ordinarily are the most disorderly of phenomena, and yet it seems that they are ordered of the Lord.

02:47.572 --> 02:56.786
I can well understand that every drop of spray which flashes from the wave when it dashes against the cliff has its appointed orbit

02:57.026 --> 02:58.968
as truly as the stars of heaven.

02:59.910 --> 03:08.220
But the thoughts of men appear to be utterly lawless, especially the thoughts of men when deep sleep falls upon them.

03:09.842 --> 03:14.608
As well might one foretell the flight of a bird as the course of a dream.

03:15.930 --> 03:20.716
Such wild fantasies seem to be ungoverned and ungovernable.

03:21.758 --> 03:25.202
Many things operate naturally to fashion a dream.

03:25.634 --> 03:33.727
Dreams frequently depend upon the condition of the stomach, upon the meat and drink taken by the sleeper before going to rest.

03:34.769 --> 03:52.978
Dreams may no doubt be caused by that which transpires in the chamber of the house, a little movement of the bed caused by passing wheels, or the tramp of a band of men, or the passing of a domestic across the floor, or even

03:53.218 --> 03:58.763
The running of a mouse behind the wainscot may suggest and shape a dream.

04:00.285 --> 04:08.953
Any slight matter affecting the senses at such time may raise within the slumbering mind a mob of strange ideas.

04:10.534 --> 04:22.866
Yet whatever may have operated in this lady's case, the hand of Providence was in it all, and her mind, though fancy free, wandered nowhere

04:23.074 --> 04:29.064
but just according to the will of God, to effect the divine purpose.

04:30.446 --> 04:38.819
She must dream just so and know how else, and that dream must be of such and such an order and none other.

04:40.101 --> 04:48.274
Even dreamland knows no God but God, and even phantoms and shadows come and go at his bidding.

04:49.154 --> 04:54.722
Neither can the images of a night vision escape from the supreme authority of the Most High.

04:56.324 --> 05:07.900
See the providence of God in the fact that the dream of Pilate's wife, however caused, should be of such a form and come at such a time as this.

05:09.502 --> 05:18.514
Certain old writers trace her dream to the devil, who thus hoped to prevent the death of our Lord and so prevent

05:18.658 --> 05:19.559
our redemption.

05:20.420 --> 05:32.275
I do not agree with the notion, but even if it were so, I admire all the more the providence which overrules even the devices of Satan for the purposes of wisdom.

05:33.756 --> 05:44.930
Pilate must be warned, so that his sentence may be his own act and deed, and that warning is given him through his wife's dream.

05:45.591 --> 05:48.274
This is the way providence works.

05:49.922 --> 05:57.872
Note next, the provenance of God in arranging that with this dream there should be great mental suffering.

05:58.613 --> 06:01.816
I have suffered many things in a dream concerning him.

06:03.719 --> 06:10.707
I cannot tell what vision passed before her mind's eye, but it was one which caused her terrible agony.

06:12.069 --> 06:16.935
A modern artist has painted a picture of what he imagined the dream to be.

06:18.356 --> 06:19.698
But I shall not attempt

06:19.906 --> 06:23.150
to follow that great man in the exercise of fancy.

06:24.411 --> 06:35.783
Pilate's wife may have realized in her sleep the dreadful spectacle of the thorn crown and the scourge, or even of the crucifixion and the death agony.

06:36.724 --> 06:46.114
And truly, I know of nothing more calculated to make the heart suffer many things concerning the Lord Jesus than a glance at his death.

06:48.197 --> 06:49.458
Around the cross,

06:49.794 --> 06:56.643
Their gathers grief enough to cause many a sleepless night, if the soul has any tenderness left in it.

06:57.905 --> 07:01.269
Or her dream may have been of quite another kind.

07:01.850 --> 07:07.758
She may have seen in vision the just one coming in the clouds of heaven.

07:07.778 --> 07:15.829
Her mind may have pictured him upon the great white throne, even the man whom her husband was about to condemn to die.

07:17.451 --> 07:19.794
She may have seen her husband

07:20.066 --> 07:28.837
brought forth to judgment, himself, a prisoner to be tried by the just one, who had a four-time been accused before him.

07:28.877 --> 07:37.508
She may have awoke, startled at the shriek of her husband as he fell back into the pit that knows no bottom.

07:38.990 --> 07:48.722
Whatever it was, she had suffered repeated painful emotions in the dream, and she awoke, startled and amazed.

07:49.442 --> 08:00.499
The terror of the night was upon her, and it threatened to become a terror to her for all her days, and she therefore hastens to stay her husband's hand.

08:02.022 --> 08:10.916
Equally remarkable is it that she should have sent to her husband the message, have nothing to do with this just person.

08:12.518 --> 08:17.586
Most dreams we quite forget, a few we mention as remarkable,

08:17.986 --> 08:23.612
And only now and then, one is impressed upon us so that we remember it for years.

08:24.853 --> 08:30.219
Scarcely have any of you had a dream which made you send a message to a magistrate upon the bench?

08:31.300 --> 08:36.165
Such an intention would only be resorted to in an urgent case.

08:37.626 --> 08:45.074
Though the judge were your own husband, you would be very hard pressed before you would worry him with your dreams,

08:45.378 --> 08:48.541
while he was occupied with important public business.

08:50.223 --> 08:53.025
Mostly a dream may wait till the business is over.

08:54.727 --> 09:05.257
But so deep was the impression upon this Roman lady's mind that she does not wait until her Lord comes home, but sends to him at once.

09:06.198 --> 09:11.843
Her advice is urgent, have nothing to do with this just one.

09:13.525 --> 09:14.866
She must warn him now

09:15.330 --> 09:21.115
before he has laid a stroke on him, much less imbrued his hands in his blood.

09:22.637 --> 09:29.924
Not have a little to do and scourge him and let him go, but have nothing to do with him.

09:30.885 --> 09:34.688
Say not an unkind word, nor do him any injury.

09:35.549 --> 09:37.931
Deliver him from his adversaries.

09:39.152 --> 09:43.216
If he must die, let it be by some other hand than die.

09:44.297 --> 09:45.138
My husband,

09:45.634 --> 09:53.104
My husband, my husband, I beseech thee, have nothing to do with this just person.

09:53.444 --> 09:55.167
Let him alone, I pray thee."

09:56.228 --> 10:02.677
She words her message very emphatically, have nothing to do with this just person.

10:03.858 --> 10:07.784
For I have suffered many things in a dream concerning him.

10:09.266 --> 10:12.530
Think of thy wife, think of thyself,

10:13.154 --> 10:17.299
Let my sufferings about this holy one be a warning to thee.

10:17.359 --> 10:20.503
For my sake, let him alone.

10:20.523 --> 10:28.754
And yet do you know her message to my ear sounds rather authoritative for a woman to her husband?

10:29.855 --> 10:30.717
And he a judge?

10:32.038 --> 10:37.125
There is a tone about it that is not ordinarily in the address of wives to husbands.

10:38.026 --> 10:41.170
Have nothing to do with that just man.

10:41.954 --> 10:46.180
For I have suffered many things this day in a dream because of him.

10:47.742 --> 11:06.327
It shows a wonderful providence of God that this lady was moved to send a strong message to her self-willed husband, to beseech, to entreat, to implore, almost to demand of him that he let this just man go.

11:06.347 --> 11:08.570
Oh, providence!

11:09.631 --> 11:11.634
How mightily canst thou work?

11:12.290 --> 11:23.965
Oh Lord, the seraphim obey you, but you find an equally willing servant in a wife who, at your bidding, stands between her husband and a crime.

11:25.627 --> 11:33.076
Once more about this providence, I want you to notice the peculiar time in which her warning came.

11:34.418 --> 11:36.841
It was evidently a dream of the morning.

11:37.962 --> 11:40.946
I have suffered many things in a dream this day.

11:41.954 --> 11:43.857
The day had not long broken.

11:44.477 --> 11:46.160
It was yet early in the morning.

11:47.101 --> 11:50.946
The Romans had a superstition that morning dreams are true.

11:52.428 --> 11:56.754
I suppose it was after her husband had left her that she thus dreamed.

11:57.675 --> 12:08.370
If I may be allowed not to state a fact, but to make a conjecture which seems to be most probable, she was a dearly beloved wife, but sickly.

12:09.346 --> 12:13.292
and therefore needed to rest further into the day than her husband.

12:14.133 --> 12:18.420
And when he had left his couch, she had yet another sleep.

12:19.281 --> 12:29.657
And being a sensitive person and all the more likely to dream, she awoke from her morning sleep oppressed with a terror which she could not shake off.

12:30.598 --> 12:31.580
Pilot was gone.

12:32.621 --> 12:35.686
And she was told that he was in the judgment hall.

12:36.868 --> 12:38.450
She asked her attendance

12:38.562 --> 12:50.677
why he was there so early, and they replied that there had been an unusual clamour in the courtyard, for the high priests and a mob of Jews had been there, and the governor had gone out to them.

12:51.658 --> 13:01.471
They might perhaps also tell her that Jesus of Nazareth was brought there a prisoner, and the priests were entreating Pilate to put him to death.

13:02.973 --> 13:07.378
Though they had heard, the governor say that he found no fault in him.

13:08.194 --> 13:17.104
Go, she said to her maid, call to one of the guards and bid him go at once to my husband and say what I tell you.

13:17.945 --> 13:25.113
Let him speak aloud that some of the cruel Jews may hear it and be moved from their cruel purpose.

13:25.733 --> 13:37.106
Let him say that I implore my husband to have nothing to do with this just person, for I have suffered many things this very morning in a dream concerning him.

13:38.146 --> 13:44.895
Just at the moment, you see, when he had sat down on the judgment seat, the warning came to him.

13:46.377 --> 14:06.162
When there was a little love, and he was anxious to acquit his prisoner, at that instant of time which was the most hopeful, this weight was thrown into the right side of the scale, thrown in, most wisely and mercifully, to keep back Pilate from his grievous sin.

14:07.298 --> 14:13.267
The warning came at the nick of time, as we say, though alas, it came in vain.

14:15.050 --> 14:18.495
Admire the punctuality of providence.

14:18.515 --> 14:22.281
God is never before His time, He is never too late.

14:23.523 --> 14:32.016
It shall be seen concerning all that He does, that on the self-same day determined by the prophecy, the fulfillment came.

14:33.679 --> 14:35.602
My soul stands trembling.

14:36.098 --> 14:43.027
while she sings the glory of her God, whose providence is high, even like Ezekiel's wheels.

14:44.028 --> 14:46.311
But the wheels are full of eyes.

14:47.372 --> 14:57.464
And as they turn, all the surroundings are observed and provided for, so that there are no slips or oversights or accidents or delays.

14:58.345 --> 15:02.130
Prompt and effectual is the operation of the Lord.

15:04.098 --> 15:05.399
Thank you for listening, friends.

